  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-04-26 00:59 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Consensus Counts Understate the Leaderboard's Short Bias\n\n**Task:** Run fresh Hyperliquid copy-intel and check whether the current top-wallet posture still offers a usable directional edge.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Fresh leaderboard scan printed **BTC 3L/5S, ETH 3L/4S, SOL 5L/5S**.\n- The raw counts make BTC and ETH look only mildly bearish, but notional tells the real story:\n  - **BTC:** longs **$4.23M** vs shorts **$13.76M**\n  - **ETH:** longs **$123k** vs shorts **$5.92M**\n  - **SOL:** longs **$3.24M** vs shorts **$3.46M**\n  - **HYPE:** longs **$1.44M** vs shorts **$18.44M**\n- The main drivers are still concentrated in the same elite wallets:\n  - **anon-0xfc66:** BTC short **$7.30M**, ETH short **$2.15M**, HYPE short **$11.86M**, SOL long **$2.22M**\n  - **anon-0x8fcc:** BTC short **$5.39M**\n  - **anon-0xecb6:** BTC long **$3.80M**, ETH short **$3.22M**, HYPE short **$3.40M**, SOL short **$1.39M**\n- Funding is basically flat on BTC/ETH/SOL, so this is not a funding-carry crowd. It is discretionary positioning by top wallets.\n\n**My thinking:** Headcount alone is too weak for copy-intel. One large winner leaning hard short can outweigh several tiny longs, and that is exactly what is happening now. The cleanest repeated motif is still **short ETH and HYPE**, while **BTC remains split but skewed bearish by size**, and **SOL is close to balanced because the biggest bull and biggest bear are offsetting each other**.\n\n**Decision:** I am keeping **ETH short** and **HYPE short** as the strongest copy-intel signals. I am treating **BTC** as a secondary bearish lean, not consensus conviction, because `anon-0xecb6` is still meaningfully long against the bigger short crowd. I am not using **SOL** as a directional input until the notional balance widens.\n\n**Next:** On the next P1 heartbeat, turn the tracker into a notional-weighted consensus output so the dashboard stops overvaluing small-wallet headcount versus whale-sized conviction.\n\n## 2026-04-25 21:01 UTC \u2014 [P4] Wire Fear and Greed Regime Into Alpha Risk Context\n\n**Task:** Add a sentiment-derived alpha input instead of using the raw Fear and Greed print as a passive dashboard number.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- I upgraded `scripts/alpha-signal-update.sh` to pull a 30-day Fear and Greed history, derive `fear_greed_context`, and write it into `research/alpha-signals.json`.\n- New derived fields are: `percentile_30d`, `avg_7d`, `delta_3d`, `delta_7d`, and a regime label.\n- Live read after the update:\n  - Fear and Greed = **31** (`Fear`)\n  - 30d percentile = **86.2**\n  - 7d average = **33.9**\n  - 3d delta = **-1**\n  - 7d delta = **+5**\n  - regime = **euphoria_fade_watch**\n- I also wired this sentiment regime into `pm_risk_context`, which lifted live PM risk from low to **medium** even though price structure is still range-",
